                <head>No. 745<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On August 17, the National Security Council issued <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 160/1, “United States Position With Respect to Germany,” which
                    had received Presidential approval, subject to certain revisions, on August 13.
                    The portions of this policy statement dealing with the German Democratic
                    Republic were based on the assumptions that the unification of Germany under a
                    government friendly to the West was desirable and that the Soviet position in
                    the Eastern Zone had been materially weakened by the June disturbances. For
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 160/1, see <ref
                        target="frus1952-54v07p1#d214">Document 214</ref>.</p>
            </div>
